# Hover Styles & Data Seeding Implementation Plan

Based on the feedback, the yellow background on the hovered service cards doesn't look good. We will change this to a lighter, sophisticated hover effect. We also need to ensure all pages (Home, Rooms, Services) show realistic hotel data with actual images.

## Proposed Changes

### 1. Fix Hover Styles for Premium Look
- **[public/css/style.css](file:///c:/wamp64/www/hotel-management/public/css/style.css)**: We will modify the `.service-item:hover` class.
  - Remove the solid `var(--primary)` yellow background on hover.
  - Implement a modern lift effect (`transform: translateY(-5px)`) with a soft, elegant box-shadow.
  - Apply a subtle gold border to retain brand consistency without overwhelming the card.
  - Smoothly scale up the hotel service icons (`transform: scale(1.1)`) to provide interactive feedback.

### 2. Populate Real Hotel Data & Images
The system already has default hotel images (rooms, team members, about sections) located in the `public/img` folder, along with database "Seeders" that link to them.
- **Run Database Seeders**: We will execute `php artisan migrate:fresh --seed` to completely refresh your local database with default realistic data. 
- This will automatically populate:
  - High-quality room data and images (`room-1.jpg`, etc.) for the **Rooms** page.
  - Elegant service listings for the **Services** page.
  - Professional team member profiles for the **About/Team** sections.

## Verification Plan
1. **Visual Testing (Hover)**: Navigate to the `services` page and hover over the "Rooms & Apartments" card to ensure the yellow background is gone and replaced by the sophisticated lift-and-shadow effect.
2. **Data Testing**: Browse the Home, Rooms, and Services pages to confirm that hotel data (room suites, prices, bed capacities) is rendering successfully with the proper high-quality images.
